it's kind of representing main sequence stars

00:01:13.230 --> 00:01:14.230
in general.

00:01:14.230 --> 00:01:20.220
If the sun were the size of a dime, then Betelgeuse
would be about three meters short of being

00:01:20.220 --> 00:01:25.330
the size of a football field including both
end zones.

00:01:25.330 --> 00:01:30.110
Since it's only three meters off, we'll say
it's the size of a football field.

00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:39.930
Now, White Dwarf would be the size of a small
bacterium, and Red Dwarf would be about the

00:01:39.930 --> 00:01:43.430
size of a sesame seed.

00:01:43.430 --> 00:01:48.160
I can kind of just number these in order right
here.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:54.980
Football fields obviously the largest, then
we go to the dime, then the sesame seed, and

00:01:54.980 --> 00:01:55.980
then the small bacterium.

00:01:55.980 --> 00:02:01.280
You've got an idea of the relative size here.

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:04.940
A sun and a white dwarf, or excuse me, the
sun and the Red Dwarf are somewhat similar

00:02:04.940 --> 00:02:09.880
in size but the small bacterium is extremely
small, and then a football field is extremely

00:02:09.880 --> 00:02:12.040
huge even compared to a dime.

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:18.980
To kind of attach some actual number of figures
to this, the sun is about 1.4 million kilometers

00:02:18.980 --> 00:02:19.980
in diameter.

00:02:19.980 --> 00:02:27.799
Then Betelgeuse is about 825 million kilometers
in diameter, located about 640 light years

00:02:27.799 --> 00:02:28.799
