00:02:28.799 --> 00:02:34.659
In fact if Betelgeuse were located in the
same place as the sun it would extend past

00:02:34.659 --> 00:02:35.800
the orbit of Jupiter.

00:02:35.800 --> 00:02:39.640
If you think about where the sun is and then
you think about the other planets and you

00:02:39.640 --> 00:02:45.870
know Jupiter is, Betelgeuse would take up
all of this area.

00:02:45.870 --> 00:02:49.019
That's how large it is, it's huge really.

00:02:49.019 --> 00:02:54.610
Now, the largest known star, which is the
hybrid giant VY Canis Majoris, is over three

00:02:54.610 --> 00:02:57.579
billion kilometers in dynam- diameter.

